<br>
The system that has abided on Erollisi Marr for around a year is one of comunication and sharing.  Da`Kor I have to acknowledge as the ones who began this system more formally with a Trakanon and Venril Sathir rotation.  Magister has carried on with the precedent set by their founding members from Da`kor even if sometimes lack of comunication leads to mishaps.  For some time they have had the number of people to kill most everything, yet usually through simple appeal to respect they don't.  Midnight Sojourn and Storm's Fury followed up in their wake and try to abide by the same system.  The system of open comunication and preplanning what guild is going to be doing what, and in the case of sometimes we are both in the same spot at the same time our earlier dealings of respect and sharing set a precedence for talking it out and coming to an agreement for that spawn with little if any resentment festering.  Affliction has earned this respect in regards to Storm's Fury and really so has Divine Grace even though sometimes they have a hard time comunicating.  <br>
<br>
United Independent has set itself up for poor interguild relations through a lack of any effort expended at communication.  Not once have I recieved a tell from anyone in United Independent without soliciting it myself by asking them.  Usually I have no idea what they are doing untill they start just showing up for a mob while we have a small preliminary group there.  Then after they get up to a size about equal to our group is when I ask them what's going on and do we want to work something out.  Often to no or little response.  Only when they feel they have the upper hand do I recieve any kind of communication from them.  Friday night it was from Mackentil and I quote, 'we have 38 here we're going to pull'.  Showing all the respect they have for any other guild or any system of working things out to prevent neanderthalic l33t d3wds from taking over Emarr.<br>
<br>
The problem we face is that each low is met with a lowering of the respect shown to other players, whom usually had nothing to do with the original offense, by the aggrieved person.  That trend continues and a slow erosion of the values of our comunity begins.  Thinking back looking for a begining to the recent(last 6months) troubles I see the Lodizal, Turtlegate as Glor put it so well, as a big player in respect going south on Emarr.  A spawn that is somewhat timeable, everyone wants and is doable with one lv 60 group if not less leads to a lot of bickering.  As well as that zone having such asinine visibility when it is snowing, yes it is 'emersive' but it leads to a hell of a lot of misunderstanding, arguing and bad blood more then it leads to a fun game.  Once one guild 'wronged' another guild on lodizal it was down hill from there with the wronged guilds doing wrong to other people etc.<br>
<br>
We must keep our standards high of what we give to our fellow players on emarr as well as what we expect.  It is imposible to receive, and quite silly to demand, respect without having shown any yourselves first.  Respect is the same on a guild level and a personal level.  Trying to seperate the two is unrealistic.  The actions of your guild, like the actions of your country, are the opinions and willingness to cooperate with the leadership in decisions they make.  Talking to individual United Independent members I cannot find one person that activly condones how the Vindicator was pulled by United Independent after Storm's Fury cleared the mobs in front of him, were ready to kill him and had a monk there actively splitting him from his guards.  But it happened anyway because not one of the people in UI who individually frowned on such an action would speak out against it.  How can you allow your name to be dragged through so much mud?  If it is the leadership then form a new guild.  Storm's Fury had Drall who was off and on an ass and we had, and deserved, a poor reputation while he was our figurehead.  The only way we changed that is through our questioning Drall on every choice he wanted and telling him no we would not cooperate in screwing over other players.  He became frustrated and quit, to the betterment of SF.  If it is a pervasive guild culture that you are a part of then please stop demanding and wondering why no one shows you any kind of respect.<br>
<br>
Don't be so absorbed in your nationalism to not realize that your neighbors are being incinerated.  Each voice raised in a no counts towards detering leadership from following a particular line of action.  If you feel the need to spout of some propagandic jargon in response to this, first take some time to actually think it over and post it well.  Just as I have done here.<br>
<br>
One thing the server cannot afford is open retaliation and bickering between a large portion of the upper tier guilds.  Can you imagine how shitty EQ would be with unguilded twink train bombs, rampant dispelling, KS groups and quite a few nasty ugly things just to screw over guilds on raids because they have totally screwed you over because they were screwed over by someone else?  I ask United Independent to think about the consequences of their actions and refusal to communicate and build up reputation and a feeling of respect.  Stealing our pull of the Vind almost resulted in a gift of our pulling the statue for you, though at an inopportune time.<br>
<br>
We as a guild will not, and cannot accept how you dealt with things on Friday.  And if there is not a change and soon in how United Independent, or any other guild in the same circumstance, acts then there will be repercussions.  If not from within the guild then from outside the guild.  Please just talk to me.  I don't hate you, I'm not a bad guy.  All I want is to be able to plan things out to lessen the impact of scarce resources.  I wont give away everything so don't bother asking for that.  I will share and have shared in the past with guilds that take time and have the patience to build up their respect, with Storm's Fury and the server in general.  And untill we have some kind of respect going we will be continuously unable to work things out when both guilds are already there.<br>
<br>
Think before you act.  Hold your guild leadership accountable for the actions of your guild as an entity.  Communicate with the people who share your server.  And one thing I learned back at orc1 in East Commonlands, don't steal other people's pulls.  <br>
