<br>
Every encounter with SF has been about numbers with UI always loosing. I have stated many times that I would like to work things out between guilds so that we do not bump heads. I sent you several tells that night but you never answered them. Gilgamel was talking to you the entire evening also. When we had the numbers to kill the mob, I said that we were going to pull. I guess you got that tell. When we pulled you had 25 people and we had 38. If you were ready you could have pulled him. UI would have backed down and left like we have down countless times in the past. We cleared the path twice which takes 40 mins. You had plenty of time to pull if you were ready.<br>
<br>
We were having a race to the mob. We didn't train you. We didn't pull through you. UI could have been in the arena with 12 people all day keeping the mobs clear also. Camping in the arena doesn't claim vindi. <br>
<br>
I don't like my name and my guild's name slandered like this. Just a couple weeks ago we were heading into fear for some epic items. SF was wanting to do CT. I told SF that he wasn't up because we had killed him the week prior and he was due to pop till the next day. We worked out a deal to let SF have CT and draco if they were up since we got them last week. We go in and CT and draco weren't up. SF leaves. About an hour later CT pops and the zone respawns. Did UI try to hide that from SF? NO! I sent a tell to SF that CT spawned. They even CR'd us. I respected the deal we worked out even though they had already left. Yep UI has no ethics.<br>
<br>
I have been playing this game forever and reading this message board forever. Everyone knows how this game is played. In the beginning usually one guild dominates. Then another guild gets the numbers to compete. The top guild doesn't back down until the up and coming guild causes them to make deals to save everyone time and prevent leaving spawns open for another less powerful guilds to kill. MS did this to Da'Kor. SF did this to MS and Da'Kor/Magister. Now SF, MS, and Magister is getting the same treatment from UI, DG, and Affliction.<br>
<br>
For the last few months Magister, MS, and SF have had free reign over SoV and the rest of Norrath. They have formed agreements to work together to keep from bumping heads and to keep other people out. Now they have competition from UI, DG, and Affliction. Now these three guilds must fight for our shot at these mobs. They will not be handed to us on a platter.<br>
<br>
After the Klandicar incident that Kaane mentioned above, UI got into the K and Z rotation with Magister, MS, and SF. It lasted about month because DG started killing them and I think Affliction got a kill or two also. Instead of allowing them into the rotation, Zlandicar went FFA (Also partly due to Klandicar being upgraded). Once again to keep other guilds out. It is very difficult to compete with Magister, MS, and SF when they are raiding. UI accepts this. If UI wants Zlandicar, we have to have the raid force ready and beat everyone there. I think it has happened once.<br>
<br>
Now Magister and MS have an agreement worked out where they swap weeks in NTov. SF, UI, DG, and Affliction must compete with whoever isn't in NToV that week. Magister has already stated that it was their statue that week but decided not to pull it. Does everyone expect Magister or MS to just let one of these guilds just have the statue spawn? You are smoking crack if you answer yes. If a raid force is there and ready to go they won't touch them. However, if another guild is just gathering, they will pull on and rightly so. This is how the game is played. If UI had not of been there I guarantee that Magister would have pulled right over SF.<br>
<br>
Something else to consider. Magister and MS can kill multiple boss mobs in one night. They just don't go kill uber mob #1 and call it a night. They kill three or four a night, heck, maybe more. I think it is amazing that they can do this. It shows how organized and powerful they really are. What this causes though is very few mobs available for everyone else. When guilds get a shot, they aren't going to back down. Would UI support rotations on uber mobs? Of course. We wouldn't have to bust our ass to get them. Would Magister and MS allow SF and UI into the rotation? HELL NO, because they don't have to. They only will do it when they get serious competition.<br>
<br>
I am not bitter about the way the game is played. I accept that the more powerful guilds make the rules. I accept that the more powerful guilds will dominate and UI has to bust our ass to get the leftovers. I do not accept being flamed for beating another guild to a mob. I do not accept being insulted for playing the game by the rules that have existed on this server for a very very very long time.<br>
<br>
